f6_assessments.q2:
As the funds allocated to this challenge are proposed to increase, feedback and measurements from previous rounds would have strengthened the case for this challenge. Some of the metrics in this challenge are very hard to measure. What does "Measured overall" mean ?

There is no discussion around these measurements:
"Proof of iteration";
"Re-election rates";
"Embracing failure";
Which are subjective in nature and open to interpretation. 

What have been some projects which met these metrics? How were they evaluated? What worked what did not work, what did the challenge team learn?
These questions would have been good to at least link to blogs about.
